Hard at first, suggest practicing on Easy, and then progressing.

Good Game

There's a few moments that felt unfair, such as being grabbed from inside a locker and enemies knowing when you are as well as having more enemies than what it should be going around.

It feels like there's a lot of bother here and there but the feeling of the game and how it scares the player lead me to forget about the Steam Refund policy (2 HR limit).

I am glad I forgot, because I enjoyed this game a lot, despite the glitches/bugs/etc that I went through :)

An excellent horror game with cool mechanics. Keeps you on your toes even after repeated playthroughs. Please add more maps, tasks and monsters! The mechanics with abilities are very cool, but require improvements, at least in terms of level increases. Don't abandon this horror game, it's a great product for the price!

This game is INSANELY good!  I saw it a long time ago and added it to my wish list based off of just the promotional clips and WOW! I had SO much fun playing this with my friends! They definitely should work a bit on their perks to make it even more replayable, but even without perfected perks, School Labyrinth was incredibly fun, scary and entertaining all in one.  I look forward to playing it again with friends! DEFINITELY GET IT!!

Very fun game with a great atmosphere. Entities are very different from each other and the game is overall very balanced.
With the randomly generated level and perks you can upgrade it has good replayability too! I highly recommend this game if you wanna have a fun and spooky game night with your friends.

ive had this game on my wish list for a long time and im happy its finally out. amazing game, the enemies scared me and my friends, especially the mimic type. the game design is very nice too, i like how the school looks and the enemies look really scary too. joining lobbies was very easy and worked good as well. one thing that NEEDS to be added is proximity chat, it would make the game feel more fun with friends. also more maps would be cool, maybe a college campus?

Excellent game! Excited to see how this game advances in the future. I believe the game needs a little bit of reworking around how the enemies AI react to the environment and players. I think something like proximity chat for this game would make the mechanic of interacting with enemies much more immersive. I PERSONALLY believe finding candles should feel a little more daunting. So I believe a difficulty increase via something like puzzles to be able to light the candles would make unique aspects to the game!

Maybe I'm getting ahead of myself but larger and new maps for this game would be a great addition. Overall however, this is such a great start to a game with decent potential! Overall, the game has got me excited to see whats in store for future updates!

This was surprisingly solid for a multiplayer horror game. it can also be played solo. We pretty much traverse a school while scavenging for supplies in order to escape it. It also features a perk system for ur survivors. The graphics are solid and the atmosphere is quite creepy. The mannequin like creatures are definitely a good choice for a school setting. Doesn't hurt that the price tag is not bad either.
